text: Stanbridge is a town/community in Leeton Shire, New South Wales, Australia. It is in the central part of the Riverina. It is situated by road, about east from Whitton, north west from Gogeldrie and west of Leeton. At the , Stanbridge had a population of 414 people. A major employer is Freedom Foods, a maker of health foods including cereals biscuits and bars. The company moved to Stanbridge from Melbourne in 2009 and employs about 76 people. ==Notes and references== Category:Towns in the Riverina Category:Towns in New South Wales Category:Leeton Shire
